      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the issue you're facing is a classic case of the product image and title not properly aligning on smaller screens. You might want to consider adding a bit of padding to the product title to give it some breathing room, like so:\n\n```css\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px; /* Adjusted from -10px to 10px */\n  padding-top: 5px; /* Added padding to create space between the image and title */\n}\n```\n\nThis should help the title sit nicely below the image, even on smaller screens. Remember, sometimes you have to give your elements a little room to breathe, just like a well-fed goblin needs space to spread its wings.",
